column2: "Yeah, this just shouldn't... This is weird."

"It's even further from established norms than the
forest data. Something about this tundra region is
wrong. It's unnatural."

"I'm not even sure how a patch of land can yield
data like this!"

"But it's starting to look like Naberius isn't the quiet
little planet we think it is. Which would mean..."

"Sorry, I should get back to the data. I'll let you
know as soon as I figure anything out."

"<%me>さん。
やっぱりこれ……おかしいです。"

"森林のデータの比じゃない……
凍土部は、異常ですよ。
こんなの不自然だ。"

"こんな無茶苦茶な環境値……
どうやって出来あがったんだろう。"

"……ナベリウスは、私たちが思うような
平穏かつ安全な惑星ではないのかも……
いえ、それ以上に……"

"ちょっと、調査に集中してみます。
何かわかったら連絡しますので。"
